{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f0f969e9-0cb6-46e9-b8af-52c2b1d77269","content":"In .NET MAUI, those `Application`-level overrides are replaced by **`Window` lifecycle events**. Override `CreateWindow` in your `Application` class and subscribe to them:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = new Window(new AppShell());\n\n    window.Created += (s, e) => { /* OnStart equivalent */ };\n    window.Stopped += (s, e) => { /* OnSleep equivalent */ };\n    window.Resumed += (s, e) => { /* OnResume equivalent */ };\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\nAlternatively, subclass `Window` and override `OnCreated()`, `OnStopped()`, and `OnResumed()`.\n\n**Key mapping:**\n| Xamarin.Forms | MAUI Window event |\n|---|---|\n| `OnStart()` | `Created` |\n| `OnSleep()` | `Stopped` |\n| `OnResume()` | `Resumed` |\n\nMAUI also adds `Activated`, `Deactivated`, and `Destroying` for finer-grained control.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ac39aee1-29b1-42c0-b641-7a8f313c8922","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating lifecycle methods from Xamarin.Forms to .NET MAUI. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing to search the codebase.\n\nIn Xamarin.Forms, you'd override `OnStart()`, `OnSleep()`, and `OnResume()` in your `Application` class.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the equivalent is to use the `Window` lifecycle events or override lifecycle methods on the `Window` class. The `Application` class no longer has `OnStart`/`OnSleep`/`OnResume`. Instead, you work with the `Window` class and its lifecycle events.\n \nIn MAUI, the mapping is straightforward: `OnStart` maps to the `Window.Created` event, `OnSleep` corresponds to `Window.Deactivated`, and `OnResume` maps to `Window.Activated`. You typically override `CreateWindow()` in your `Application` class to set up a custom `Window` subclass where you can subscribe to these lifecycle events.","outputTokens":698,"requestId":"4837:8197A:7656F1F:82A1DDB:69F3FB3E"},"id":"afeb958d-64fb-4ce5-9da6-224e063e8620","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:00:58.765Z","parentId":"29b2b2d9-3e82-441e-afc8-2d4a2ef16aa5"}
